{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We use the activity indices introduced for the MRS Hα spectral data in He et al (2023) to measure Hα activity intensity.",
    "The primary measure of Hα activity intensity is the Hα activity index (denoted by I Hα), which is defined as the ratio of the mean flux in the central band of the Hα line to the mean flux in the two continuum bands on the two sides of the line.",
    "To evaluate I Hα index, the width of the central band of the Hα line in MRS data is set to 0.25 Å, and the two continuum bands are both 25 Å away from the Hα line center and 5 Å in width (He et al, 2023).",
    "The wavelength shift in the MRS spectral data caused by radial velocity is corrected by using the rv r0 parameter provided in the MRS catalog (see Section 3.1.3).",
    "Because the value of the I Hα index depends on the continuum flux, which is a function of stellar atmospheric parameters, the Hα R-index (denoted by R Hα) is introduced as the secondary measure of Hα activity intensity, which is defined as the ratio of Hα luminosity to bolometric luminosity."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We use the activity indices introduced for the MRS Hα spectral data in He et al (2023) to measure Hα activity intensity.",
    "To evaluate I Hα index, the width of the central band of the Hα line in MRS data is set to 0.25 Å, and the two continuum bands are both 25 Å away from the Hα line center and 5 Å in width (He et al, 2023)."
  ]
}